00025 /*! \file psht_perftest.c
00026     Performance test of libpsht's map synthesis and analysis algorithms.
00027 
00028     This program creates a list of transform jobs with a user-specified
00029     maximum multipole lmax that operate on a HEALPix, ECP or Gaussian grid.
00030     Depending on the geometry type, the user has to specify the Nside parameter
00031     (for HEALPix) or the number of pixels per ring.
00032     The individual job types are also given by the user
00033     and can be "alm2map", "map2alm", "alm2map_pol", "map2alm_pol",
00034     "alm2map_spin[1-3]", "map2alm_spin[1-3]", and "alm2map_deriv1".
00035     Any combination of job types is allowed.
00036 
00037     All requested jobs are executed simultaneously.
00038 
00039     Copyright (C) 2006-2010 Max-Planck-Society
00040     \author Martin Reinecke
00041 */
00042 
00043 #include <stdio.h>
00044 #include <stdlib.h>
00045 #include <string.h>
00046 #include "psht.h"
00047 #include "psht_geomhelpers.h"
00048 #include "psht_almhelpers.h"
00049 #include "c_utils.h"
00050 #include "walltime_c.h"

00052 static void get_map(float **map, ptrdiff_t npix)
00053   {
00054   *map=RALLOC(float,npix);
00055   SET_ARRAY(*map,0,npix,1);
00056   }
00057 static void get_alm(pshts_cmplx **alm, ptrdiff_t nalm)
00058   {
00059   static const pshts_cmplx pshts_cmplx_one={1,1};
00060   *alm=RALLOC(pshts_cmplx,nalm);
00061   SET_ARRAY(*alm,0,nalm,pshts_cmplx_one);
00062   }
00063 
00064 static void prepare_job (const char *jobname, float **map,
00065   pshts_cmplx **alm, ptrdiff_t npix, ptrdiff_t nalm, int ofs_m, int ofs_a,
00066   int num_m, int num_a)
00067   {
00068   int m;
00069   printf("adding job: %s\n", jobname);
00070   for (m=0; m<num_m; ++m)
00071     get_map (&map[ofs_m+m],npix);
00072   for (m=0; m<num_a; ++m)
00073     get_alm (&alm[ofs_a+m],nalm);
00074   }
